, 
<figureCitation box="[293,323,402,426]" captionStart="FIGURES 56–69" captionStartId="93.[151,263,1811,1834]" captionTargetBox="[176,1418,181,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-173@93.[176,1420,181,1791]" captionTargetPageId="93" captionText="FIGURES 56–69. Leptomorphus wings. 56. L. furcatus paratype male, dorsal. 57. L. gracilis, ventral. 58. L. grjebinei, ventral. 59. L. hyalinus, ventral. 60. L. magnificus, ventral. 61. L. mandelai holotype male, ventral. 62. L. medleri, ventral. 63. L. nebulosus dark form, dorsal. Arrow indicates cell r4 (contains an extra vein in this specimen). 64. L. nebulosus light form, dorsal. 65. L. neivai ventral. 66. L. obscurus ventral. 67. L. ornatus ventral. 68. L. panorpiformis ventral. 69. L. perplexus paratype female, dorsal. Abbreviations: A1, A2 = Anal veins; C = costa; CuA = anterior branch of cubitus; CuP = posterior branch of cubitus; h = humeral crossvein; M1,M2,M4, = branches of the media; r-m = radial-medial crossvein; Rs = radial sector vein; R1, R4, R5 = branches of the radius; Sc = subcosta; sc-r = subcostal-radial crossvein." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">56</figureCitation>
